INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '935ee07c-e7ca-4d23-9ba2-24cca7097355',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$webpack Plugin System — Hooking Into the Compiler Lifecycle$escape$,
  $escape$webpack's plugin system is built on Tapable, a hook library that exposes the internal compiler and compilation objects at every stage of the build. Plugins tap into these hooks to read or mutate build state.

The two core objects are `compiler` (the long-lived webpack instance) and `compilation` (a single build run). Each exposes typed hooks — `SyncHook`, `AsyncSeriesHook`, `SyncBailHook`, etc. — that fire at defined lifecycle points: `compiler.hooks.run`, `compilation.hooks.optimizeChunkModules`, `compilation.hooks.processAssets`, and dozens more.

A plugin is just an object with an `apply(compiler)` method. Inside, you tap hooks with `.tap()` (sync), `.tapAsync()` (callback), or `.tapPromise()` (Promise). The `processAssets` hook, for example, lets you inject, replace, or remove emitted files before they hit disk — useful for inlining manifests, rewriting hashes, or generating reports.

Hook execution order is deterministic: taps fire in registration order within a stage, and `AsyncSeriesHook` chains them sequentially, ensuring each plugin's async work completes before the next runs.$escape$,
  $escape$class InjectBuildMetaPlugin {
  apply(compiler) {
    compiler.hooks.thisCompilation.tap('InjectBuildMetaPlugin', (compilation) => {
      compilation.hooks.processAssets.tapPromise(
        {
          name: 'InjectBuildMetaPlugin',
          stage: compiler.webpack.Compilation.PROCESS_ASSETS_STAGE_ADDITIONS,
        },
        async (assets) => {
          const meta = JSON.stringify({ builtAt: Date.now() });
          compilation.emitAsset(
            'build-meta.json',
            new compiler.webpack.sources.RawSource(meta)
          );
        }
      );
    });
  }
}

module.exports = { plugins: [new InjectBuildMetaPlugin()] };$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
